This paper deals with a machine learning problem of detecting novel instances in a multi-instance multi-label (MIML) setting. The paper discusses the application of this problem in image tagging, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) domains. The proposed method is based on a discriminative framework, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of unlabeled data, which is a common theme in information retrieval (cs.IR). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.IR, and cs.CL.
